    "content": "<h1>Simon the Zealot</h1><h2>Facts:</h2><p>Simon the Zealot was one of Jesus’ twelve disciples.</p><ul><li><p>Simon is mentioned three times in the listing of Jesus’ disciples, but little else is known about him.</p></li><li><p>Simon was one of the Eleven who met to pray together in Jerusalem after Jesus went back up into heaven.</p></li><li><p>The term “zealot” may mean that Simon was a member of “the Zealots,” a Jewish religious party that was very zealous in upholding the Law of Moses while strongly opposing the Roman government.</p></li><li><p>Or, “zealot” may simply mean “the zealous one,” referring to Simon’s religious zeal.</p></li></ul><p>(Translation suggestions: How to Translate Names)</p><p>(See also: <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25466\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">apostle</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25669\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">disciple</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"26296\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">the twelve</span>)</p><h2>Bible References:</h2><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:12-Acts1:14\">Acts 1:12–14</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:14-Luke6:16\">Luke 6:14–16</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:17-Mark3:19\">Mark 3:17–19</a></p></li></ul><h2>Word Data:</h2><ul><li><p>Strong’s: G22080, G25810, G46130</p></li></ul>",
